Step 1: Calculate Gross Profit Margin  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
• From the income statement:  
 - Gross Profit = 8,372,608.70  
 - Total Revenue = 28,572,608.70  
• Compute:  
 Gross Profit Margin = (8,372,608.70 ÷ 28,572,608.70) × 100% ≈ 29.30%

Step 2: Calculate Cash Flow to Debt Ratio  
• Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities ÷ Total Debt)  
• In this context, Total Debt is represented by Total Current Liabilities, which is 8,028,630.43 (from the balance sheet).  
• The Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities from the cash flow statement is -10,442,735.47  
• Compute:  
 Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = -10,442,735.47 ÷ 8,028,630.43 ≈ -1.30

Thus, the answers are:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "29.30%",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-1.30"
  }
}
